The Chronicle  Thandeka Moyo-Ndlovu, Online Reporter A Bulawayo man (47) from Burnside lost four fingers after he sustained injuries when a hand grenade that he was using as a keyholder exploded. The man, who is a gardener, found the grenade on New Year’s Day as he was going about his duties. Bulawayo police spokesperson Inspector Abednico Ncube said the man showed the grenade to his friend. <img class="size-large wp-image-570156" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/09/Inspector-Abednico-Ncube--680x380.jpeg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/09/Inspector-Abednico-Ncube-.jpeg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/09/Inspector-Abednico-Ncube--360x200.jpeg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Inspector Abednico Ncube “On January 12 at around 3 PM, he pulled the safety pin of the hand grenade and it exploded twice in his right hand. He was injured on the right-hand palm and was taken to United Bulawayo Hospital where he is currently admitted. Four right-hand fingers and half of the palm have been amputated,” said Insp Ncube. “Members of the public are hereby advised and warned to take or consider any unknown metal as a dangerous object. Regrettably, a 47-year-old male took a deadly grenade for a key holder.” @thamamoe 